    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When you set a new session preset on your capture session or select a different "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturedevice/1389221-activeformat"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " on your capture device, you can query or observe changes to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturedevice/2968216-activemaxexposureduration"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can override this property at any time, to any value in the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturedevice/1389221-activeformat"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturedeviceformat/1624592-minexposureduration"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcapturedeviceformat/1624582-maxexposureduration"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " range. Changes are reflected immediately while the session is running, with no graph rebuilding. You can also set the property to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coremedia/kcmtimeinvalid"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to return to the default value. For example, one case in which you'd override the auto-exposure algorithm's maximum exposure duration is if you want shorter exposure than your frame rate. If you need to freeze motion by exposing for 1/40th of a second but still capture 30 frames a second, then a manual override is needed. "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
